fingen, Neckarkreis, Wuerttemberg":"Sindelfingen, Böblingen, Württemberg, Germany","Germany":"Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Riehm","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German:","from Middle High German <i>rieme</i> ‘band, strap’, hence a metonymic occupational name for a (leather) strap maker, or a nickname for a wearer of such items.","topographic name from the same word as 1 in the sense ‘narrow strip of land’, or a habitational name from Riem near Munich. Compare   Reams  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Reams","meanings":["English (Lincolnshire): of Norman origin, a habitational name from Rames in Seine-Maritime (France). This surname is rare in Britain. Compare   Rheams  .","Americanized form of German   Riehm  ."]},{"name":"Ream","meanings":["Perhaps an Americanized form of German   Riehm  ,   Rehm  , or <b>Röhm</b> (see   Roehm  ).","English: perhaps a nickname from Middle English <i>reaume</i>, <i>reame</i> ‘realm, dominion’, although the context for the adoption of this word as a surname is unclear."]}]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Riehm was born in 1485, in Sindelfingen, Böblingen, Württemberg, Germany, her father, Everhart Riehm, was 20 and her mother, Fräulein Everhart Riehm, was 15. She married Hans Schäffer in 1519, in Sindelfingen, Böblingen, Baden-Württemberg, Germany. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1535, in Germany, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1485–1535":"1485–1535","1490–1550":"1490–1550","1501–1555":"1501–1555","1518–1572":"1518–1572","1524–1607":"1524–1607","1465–1509":"1465–1509","1470–Female":"1470–Surnud","1572":"1572","1550":"1550","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","1524":"1524","1535":"1535","1501":"1501","1555":"1555","1465":"1465","1485":"1485","1509":"1509","1519":"1519","1607":"1607","1518":"1518","Leimen, Heidelberg, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Leimen, Rhein-Neckar-Kreis, Baden-Württemberg, Saksamaa","Leimen, Leimen, Rhein-Neckar-Kreis, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Leimen, Rhein-Neckar-Kreis, Baden-Württemberg, Saksamaa","Sindelfingen, Böblingen, Baden-Württemberg, Deutschland":"Sindelfingen, Kreis Böblingen, Baden-Württemberg, Saksamaa","Ottenhausen, Straubenhardt, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Ottenhausen, Straubenhardt, Enzkreis, Baden-Württemberg, Saksamaa","of Sindelfingen, Neckarkreis, Wuerttemberg":"Sindelfingen, Kreis Böblingen, Württemberg, Saksamaa","Germany":"Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1485–1535":"1485–1535","1490–1550":"1490–1550","1501–1555":"1501–1555","1518–1572":"1518–1572","1524–1607":"1524–1607","1465–1509":"1465–1509","1470–Female":"1470–Kuollut","1572":"1572","1550":"1550","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","1524":"1524","1535":"1535","1501":"1501","1555":"1555","1465":"1465","1485":"1485","1509":"1509","1519":"1519","1607":"1607","1518":"1518","Leimen, Heidelberg, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Leimen, Rhein-Neckar-Kreis, Baden-Württemberg, Saksa","Leimen, Leimen, Rhein-Neckar-Kreis, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Leimen, Rhein-Neckar-Kreis, Baden-Württemberg, Saksa","Sindelfingen, Böblingen, Baden-Württemberg, Deutschland":"Sindelfingen, Kreis Böblingen, Baden-Württ